INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(1,1,NULL,'CSA Quick Revision Dump Built from your uploaded question sets. 1. A Service Catalog may include which components? A. Order Guides, Exchange Rates, Calendars B. Order Guides, Catalog Items, and Interceptors C. Catalog Items, Asset Contracts, Task Surveys D. Record Producers, Order Guides, and Catalog Items Answer: D One-line: Service Catalog core components are Catalog Items, Order Guides, and Record Producers. 2. What happens when coalesce fields match during import? A. Existing record updated B. No Transform Map created C. New record created D. Existing record updated if no match Answer: A One-line: Coalesce updates existing records when a match is found. 3. What does a metric do? A. Homepage gauge B. Time measurement for workflows/SLAs C. Measures ITSM effectiveness D. Comparative flow measurement Answer: B One-line: Metrics measure time-based performance like SLA durations. 4. What controls variable display sequence in Catalog Items?',0,1,'08be22b2-cf6e-4e24-b23d-788e52bddd6f','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(2,1,NULL,'A. Default Value B. Sequence C. Order field D. Choice field Answer: C One-line: Variable order is controlled using the Order field. 5. Reports can be created from? (Choose 2) A. List column heading B. Metrics module C. Statistics module D. View/Run module Answers: A, D One-line: Reports are commonly created from list headers and View/Run module. 6. Knowledge Base search results can be sorted by? (Choose 3) A. Most recent update B. Popularity C. Relevancy D. Manager assignment E. Number of views Answers: A, B, C One-line: KB articles are sorted by relevance, popularity, and recency. 7. Path to fulfillment task list? A. RITM > REQ > PROCUREMENT B. REQ > RITM > PROCUREMENT C. REQ > RITM > TASK D. FULFILLMENT > RITM > TASK Answer: C One-line: Request flow is REQ → RITM → TASK.',1,2,'8569b116-034e-4aa9-a89c-ce09fba67fea','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(3,1,2,'8. Menus/modules accessed quickly and often are called? A. Breadcrumb B. Favorite C. Tag D. Bookmark Answer: B One-line: Favorites store frequently used modules and menus. 9. What is generated after ordering from Service Catalog? A. Change Request B. Order Guide C. Request D. SLA Answer: C One-line: A Service Catalog order creates a Request (REQ). 10. Actions available from User menu? (Choose 3) A. Send Notifications B. Log Out C. Elevate Roles D. Impersonate Users E. Order Catalog F. Approve Records Answers: B, C, D One-line: User menu supports logout, role elevation, and impersonation. 11. Buttons, links, context menu items are examples of? A. Business Rule B. UI Action',2,3,'d751d1b7-b62a-472d-b75a-431b90af488d','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(4,1,1,'C. Client Script D. UI Policy Answer: B One-line: UI Actions create buttons, links, and menu actions. 12. Service Catalog Items are? A. Behind the scenes B. Building blocks C. Optional D. Provide options Answer: B One-line: Catalog Items are the core building blocks of Service Catalog. 13. ACL processing order? A. Wildcard → Parent → Table B. Table → Parent → Wildcard C. Parent → Table → Wildcard D. Wildcard → Table → Parent Answer: A One-line: ACLs process from generic to specific. 14. Platform name for User table? A. u_users B. sys_users C. x_users D. sys_user Answer: D One-line: User table name is sys_user. 15. REQ number represents?',3,4,'f4f41664-1cfd-442c-a799-17a88ce190ab','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(5,1,NULL,'A. Order number B. Stage C. Task D. Individual item Answer: A One-line: REQ represents the overall request/order. 16. What would NOT appear in Application Navigator History? A. Records B. UI Pages C. Lists D. Forms Answer: B One-line: UI Pages do not appear in navigation history. 17. Update Set recommendation? A. Avoid Default Update Set B. Instances must differ in version C. Use Baseline Update Set D. Reopen completed update sets Answer: A One-line: Never use Default Update Set for migrations. 18. What initiates a Flow? A. Trigger B. Core Action C. Spoke D. Event Answer: A One-line: Every flow starts with a Trigger.',4,5,'e5d701c3-76b5-41fc-b20b-66fbb19e1c8c','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(6,1,NULL,'19. Characteristic of Catalog variables? A. Only in Record Producers B. Only in Order Guides C. Cannot affect price D. Global by default Answer: D One-line: Service Catalog variables are global by default. 20. Column Context Menu does what? A. Quick reports/configure/export B. Filtering/tags/search C. List filtering/viewing D. Form relationship actions Answer: A One-line: Column context menus support reporting, configuration, and export actions. 21. Module to create Notifications? A. System Notification > Email > Notifications B. Administration > Notification Overview C. System Properties > Email D. User Preferences > Notifications Answer: A One-line: Notifications are created under System Notification → Email. 22. KPI signals supporting workflow stability? A. Long-term signals B. Non-signals C. Anti-signals D. Stability signals Answer: D One-line: Stability signals support long-term workflow analysis.',5,6,'97b2f233-1418-43e8-950c-531ac3c2e2df','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(7,1,2,'23. UI Policy can make fields hidden/read-only/mandatory. A. True B. False Answer: A One-line: UI Policies control visibility, mandatory, and read-only behavior. 24. Business Rules enforce mandatory fields on forms. A. True B. False Answer: B One-line: Mandatory enforcement is mainly done with UI Policies or Dictionary settings. 25. Number of common interface types? Answer: 6 One-line: Homepage, List, Form, Dashboard, Maps, Timelines. 26. Benefits of Flow Designer? (Choose 3) A. 3rd-party integrations B. IDE scripting C. Natural-language logic D. No-code development E. Auto SLA creation F. Complex coding APIs Answers: A, C, D One-line: Flow Designer focuses on low-code automation and integrations. 27. Path to table configuration page?',6,7,'ef8f3c93-1aa4-4f52-95ed-db171fa1d6c4','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(8,1,NULL,'A. View > Table B. Configure > Table C. Configure > Dictionary D. View > Show Table Answer: B One-line: Table configuration is accessed via Configure → Table. 28. Role required to import knowledge articles? A. sn_knowledge_import B. sn_knowledge_contribute C. Can contribute D. Can import Answer: A One-line: sn_knowledge_import role allows KB article imports. 29. Relationship between Incident and Task tables? A. Many-to-many B. One-to-many C. Incident extends Task D. Related via INC number Answer: C One-line: Incident is a child table extending Task. 30. Records created after catalog order? (Choose 2) A. sc_task B. sc_req_item C. Change D. Incident E. Problem Answers: A, B One-line: Catalog orders create Requested Items and Catalog Tasks.',7,8,'39e64e08-3844-4f8f-bf25-6ddb5ef6e7bb','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(9,1,NULL,'31. How to show Save button on form header? A. Turn on glide.ui.advanced B. Form Design C. Turn on Save property D. Form Layout Answer: A One-line: glide.ui.advanced enables additional form controls. 32. How do flows reference record data? A. Drag table icon B. Condition Builder C. Source table on pill list D. Drag Data Pill Answer: D One-line: Flow Designer uses Data Pills for referencing data. 33. Technique for accessing referenced fields across tables? A. Table-Walking B. Sys_ID Pulling C. Dot-Walking D. Record-Hopping Answer: C One-line: Dot-walking retrieves data through reference fields. 34. Ways to assign task to yourself? (Choose 2) A. Person icon B. Edit Assigned To C. Assign To Me from list header D. Right-click → Assign to me E. Assign from form',8,9,'3cc9102a-5ff0-4848-8ce9-ba7ff053c820','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(10,1,NULL,'Answers: C, D One-line: Tasks can be self-assigned directly from list actions.',9,10,'cc345233-5946-4ad2-93be-ba5bef144512','2026-05-15 08:45:42','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(11,2,NULL,'1. What section on a task record would you use to see the most recent update made to a record? i) Journal ii) Timeline iii) update log iv) audit log v) diary vi) activity 2. What are examples of UI actions, relating to lists? choose four answers? a) List buttons b) list context menu c) list choices d) list links e) list control f) lists overwrite 3. which feature allows you to automate business logic for a particular application or process such as approvals, task, notifications, and record Operations? a) Flows b) Action sequence c) Flow diagrams d) action sets e) task flows 4. when a Flow runs an action, it generates a runtime value, which stays the same for the duration of the flow. what is the name of that runtime value? a) data pill runtime value b) sequence runtime value c) starting runtime value d) trigger runtime value e) input runtime value 5. the employee on-boarding team has asked for a way for managers to order computers, monitors, business cards, and cell phones for new employees. how would you proceed to meet this requirement? a) create order guide b) create requested item c) create record producer d) create on boarding bot 6. which resource would you use to determine if a specific user could contribute to a particular knowledge base? a) User criteria diagnostics',0,1,'0fce5006-6153-4273-99a9-aea65d8ba3ca','2026-05-15 08:45:45','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(12,2,NULL,'b) Sn_kb_author role c) User criteria job log d) knowledge author group e) KB author group 7. If a knowledge base has no access details specified. what users are able to read articles in that knowledge base? a) no users b) itil users c) users with kb_user roleproduct',1,2,'2c01028d-806c-4f07-8a78-64d407382d56','2026-05-15 08:45:45','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(13,2,NULL,'d) any user with an articles for permalink e) any active user 8. while showing a customer their incident form, they ask to change the priority field title to display their internal terminology Pvalue. how would you do that? choose two answers? c) right click on priority and select configure display settings d) right click on priority and select configure column 9. what access does a user need to be able to import articles to a knowledge base? a) Sn_Knowledge_import b) Sn_knowledge_cont ribute c) can contribute d) sn_knowledge_write e) can write f) can import 10. what controls the publishing and retiring process for knowledge articles? a) workflow designer b) workflows c) state life cycle d) approval policies e) approval definitions 11. what is an advantage of defining relationship types between ci classes? a) Improves data quality, as the CIs will automatically be related when CMDB is activated. b) it prevents users from relating CIs incorrectly. c) it automates the loading of the ci dependency view. d) makes relating CIs easier, because predefined relationship suggests which type of CIs should be 12. when using the CI dependency view, how would you view the relationship between one CI and another CI? a) right click, view relationship b) Click on the plus to expand cluster c) click down arrow, view relationship d) Hover on connection line 13. Of the Ci tables, which is a base table of the CMDB hierarchy? a) ECMDB b) Cmdb_rel_ci c) Cmdb _ci d) cmdb a) right click on priority and select configure dictionary b) right click on priority and select configure label',2,3,'c9b8bd8d-b266-4a30-b857-c555fc8d1534','2026-05-15 08:45:45','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(14,2,NULL,'e) Ecmdb_rel_ci f) Ecmdb_ci 14. what table acts as a staging area for records imported from a data source? a) staging table b) temp table c) transform table d) import set row table 15. which field (or fields) is used as a unique key during imports? a) Sys IDs',3,4,'57b945fe-e4b2-4a13-baa8-fb3b5cc02847','2026-05-15 08:45:45','CSA');
INSERT INTO "chunks" VALUES(15,2,NULL,'b) match fields c) coalesce fields d) key fields 16. what module enables an administrator to define destinations for imported data on any ServiceNow table? a) field transform b) schema map c) import map d) transform map 17. the customer wants all users to have access to the records in the offerings table. what setting on access control definition would you use to grant access to all of the offering table records? a) Offering. None b) None. Offering c) Offering. Name d) Offering 18. a manager wants to review a snapshot of month end sales performance data, as compared to sales target. in addition, the manager wants to able to see those monthly numbers trended overtime and forecasted into the future. what capability do you suggest for this manager? a) schedule reports, accustoms snapshot table and projection report b) scheduled reports, a custom snapshot table and a trend report. c) performance analytics. d) scheduled reports and excel e) key performance indicators. 19. which component of a table contains a piece of data for one record? a) Field b) Factor c) data point d) item e) element 20. what do you click when you have made modifications to your report, and you want to see the results without saving? a) Run b) Execute c) Test d) Preview e) try it 21. The report designer contains different sections for configuring your report. which section is used to specify grouping and calculations to be run against the data? a) Data',4,5,'52a7c02a-ac6f-4cd4-be80-77908ac8616d','2026-05-15 08:45:45','CSA');
